The methods used to develop these guidelines adhered to the suggested principles for developing transparent, evidence-based WHO guidelines. 8, 9 The decision to convene an international rapid advice guidelines panel for the treatment and chemoprophylaxis of H5N1 virus infection was made in January, 2006; review and preparation of the evidence summaries began in February, 2006 ; and the panel met on March 28 and 29, 2006 . 